Privacy Policy for NoTrack Browser Extension


1. Introduction
NoTrack is a privacy-focused browser extension designed to protect users by detecting and blocking web trackers while providing security status information about websites. We are committed to protecting your privacy and being transparent about our data practices.

2. Information We Collect
Our extension collects and processes the following types of data:

a) Website Content
- We analyze website content solely to detect tracking scripts and elements
- This analysis is performed locally in your browser
- No website content is stored permanently or transmitted to external servers

b) Location Information
- We process IP addresses as part of our web request monitoring system
- This information is used only for tracker detection functionality
- IP addresses are processed locally and are not stored or transmitted

3. How We Use Information
- All data processing occurs locally within your browser
- Information is used exclusively for detecting and blocking trackers
- Data is stored temporarily in your browser's memory
- All collected data is automatically cleared when browser tabs are closed

4. Data Storage and Security
- All data is processed and stored locally on your device
- No data is transmitted to external servers
- No personal information is collected or stored
- Temporary data is automatically cleared when closing tabs

5. Third-Party Access
- We do not share any data with third parties
- We do not collect or transmit any information to external servers
- All processing is done locally within your browser

6. Your Rights and Choices
- The extension can be disabled or removed at any time
- No personal data is collected, stored, or transmitted
- You maintain complete control over the extension's functionality

7. Changes to Privacy Policy
We may update this privacy policy from time to time. Any changes will be reflected in the "Last Updated" date at the top of this policy.

8. Contact Information
For any questions or concerns about this privacy policy or our data practices, please contact us at [Your Contact Information].

9. Compliance
This extension is designed with privacy as its core principle and complies with major data protection regulations including GDPR and CCPA.
